 ;; ==========================================================================
 ;; 6. POLICY — open knobs ON the operator (deferred per directive)
 ;; ==========================================================================
 :policy
 {:who-supplies-v   "#{:operator :pilot-autonomous} — supervised vs full-auto; substitutable per M-vsatarcs-writer §D1 (:operator|:autopen|:cached-policy)"
  :which-γ-merges   "operator selects which explored branch replays into master; deferred — not part of the operator's definition"
  :note "the formalism (objects, operator, V1..V5) does NOT depend on these; they are choices about how the operator is driven"}

 ;; ==========================================================================
 ;; 8. FORK RESOLUTION — how v is chosen at a fork when no operator is present
 ;;    (the precondition for overnight / autonomous WM operation)
 ;; ==========================================================================
 :fork-resolution
 {:why "For the WM to run overnight, EVAL must select v autonomously at forks. Selection is NOT 'always top-ranked' — it is pattern-warranted and RECORDED, so the choice is auditable and defeasible. Operator preference is a SIGNAL, not a gate (operator-not-sovereign): a well-warranted autonomous choice that differs from operator preference is admissible."
  :procedure
  [{:step 1 :name :enumerate :do "list the candidate directions (fork options)"}
   {:step 2 :name :pattern-warrant
    :do "score each option against futon3/library/ patterns; select the stronger pattern-based warrant; record the patterns invoked in the turn-record under :fork-warrant. Most forks resolve here ('the choice is simple')."}
   {:step 3 :name :escalate-if-close
    :do "when warrants are close or directly contested, run the AIF² contest (futon5/README-aif+.md §11 contest pattern + §12 AIF²): treat the two options as paired AIF+ lifeforms, find the fixed-point (mutual-eradication vs scope-restricted coalescence). Reserve for genuinely hard forks."}
   {:step 4 :name :record
    :do "selected option, losing option, and warrant are written into the γ frame so an operator (or later loop) can audit or overturn it."}]
  :worked-example
  {:fork "address-sorry sorry/mission-aif-head-not-served — (A) fix the mission_head load blocker → honor the WM #1 recommendation → real closure; (B) sidestep to an easier sorry for a faster demo"
   :selected :A
   :patterns-for-A
   ["futon-theory/stop-the-line — the load blocker IS a stop-the-line; B force-pushes around a halt"
    "structure/what-problem-is-this-actually-solving — the WM ranked the blocker #1; B drifts to a proxy problem"
    "war-machine/operational-not-decorative — a demo that bypasses the blocker is decorative; A makes the head operational"
    "war-machine/ideal-actual-gap — the blocker is the computable ideal/actual gap; A closes it"
    "futon-theory/all-or-nothing — a workaround is a soft partial-load; A keeps the system whole/consistent"
    "aif/niche-construction — the load-failure is a niche-construction signal (extend the substrate), not noise to route around"
    "futon-theory/wyrd — 'mere demo' collapse is the suppress-the-honest-interval anti-pattern"]
   :verified "all 7 pattern files exist in futon3/library/ (checked 2026-05-29); the 'work-around/coverage-retreat' satisficing signatures are NOT library patterns and were dropped rather than cited"
   :note "warrant fell to A; operator independently preferred A; the rule would stand on disagreement"}}

 ;; ==========================================================================
 ;; 7. D&G NOTE — subordinate to the formalism
 ;; ==========================================================================
 :dg-note
 "State apparatus = striated space (fixed coordinates, delivered endpoints — the teleport regime, :V2 violation). War Machine = smooth space (vectors, continuous variation — nomos). The REPL keeps work differential; v·∇ is the war machine proper. Exteriority-to-the-State = the freedom in who supplies v (:policy)."

 :watchwords "Difficult to realize; obvious to the wise."}
